FBIS3-57973 "drweu003__a94034" FBIS-WEU-94-003-A Document Type:Daily Report 5 January 1994 ANNEX Italy & Vatican City Annual Inflation Rate Lowest Since 1969 BR3012125293 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1039 GMT 30 Dec 93--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR3012125293 Rome ANSAMAIL Database Language: English Article Type:BFN [Unattributed article: "Inflation Confirmed at 4 Percent"] [Text] Rome, 30 Dec (ANSA) -- Inflation fell to an annual rate of 4 percent in December, ending the year at the lowest level since 1969, the national statistics bureau, ISTAT, confirmed Thursday [29 December]. ISTAT said preliminary figures taken in eight sample cities earlier this month and confirmed today showed consumer prices remained stock-still in December, bringing inflation to a 24-year low. Below is a table showing monthly inflation rates from 1987 to the present: Month 1987 1988 1989 1990 1991 1992 1993 January 4.5 5.0 5.7 6.4 6.5 6.1 4.3 February 4.2 4.9 6.3 6.2 6.7 5.4 4.5 March 4.2 4.9 6.4 6.1 6.6 5.6 4.2 April 4.2 5.0 6.7 5.8 6.7 5.6 4.2 May 4.2 4.9 6.8 5.7 6.8 5.7 4.0 June 4.1 4.9 7.0 5.6 6.9 5.5 4.1 July 4.4 4.9 7.0 5.7 6.7 5.5 4.4 August 4.5 5.0 6.7 6.3 6.3 5.3 4.4 September 5.0 4.8 6.6 6.3 6.2 5.2 4.2 October 5.3 4.7 6.8 6.2 6.1 5.0 4.3 November 5.2 5.3 6.4 6.5 6.2 4.9 4.2 December 5.1 5.5 6.5 6.4 6.0 4.8 4.0.
